SIMPLE: meal
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meal
<hw>Meal</hw> <pr>(m⟦emac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>mele</ets>, AS. <ets>m⟦aemac⟧l</ets> part, portion, portion of
time; akin to E. <ets>meal</ets> a repast. Cf.
<er>Piecemeal</er>.]</ety> <def>A part; a fragment; a portion.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Meal
<hw>Meal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mel</ets>; akin to E.
<ets>meal</ets> a part, and to D. <ets>maal</ets> time, meal, G.
<ets>mal</ets> time, <ets>mahl</ets> meal, Icel. <ets>m⟦amac⟧l</ets>
measure, time, meal, Goth. <ets>m⟦emac⟧l</ets> time, and to E.
<ets>measure</ets>. See <er>Measure</er>.]</ety> <def>The portion of
food taken at a particular time for the satisfaction of appetite; the
quantity usually taken at one time with the purpose of satisfying
hunger; a repast; the act or time of eating a meal; <as>as, the traveler
has not eaten a good <ex>meal</ex> for a week; there was silence during
the <ex>meal</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What strange fish⟦br⟧
Hath made his <qex>meal</qex> on thee?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Meal
<hw>Meal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mele</ets>, AS.
<ets>melu</ets>, <ets>melo</ets>; akin to D. <ets>meel</ets>, G.
<ets>mehl</ets>, OHG. <ets>melo</ets>, Icel. <ets>mj⟦oum⟧l</ets>, SW.
<ets>mj⟦oum⟧l</ets>, Dan. <ets>meel</ets>, also to D. <ets>malen</ets>
to grind, G. <ets>mahlen</ets>, OHG., OS., & Goth. <ets>malan</ets>,
Icel. <ets>mala</ets>, W. <ets>malu</ets>, L. <ets>molere</ets>, Gr.
<grk>my`lh</grk> mill, and E. <ets>mill</ets>. ⟦root⟧108. Cf.
<er>Mill</er>, <er>Mold</er> soil, <er>Mole</er> an animal,
<er>Immolate</er>, <er>Molar</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Grain (esp. maize, rye, or oats) that is coarsely
ground and unbolted; also, a kind of flour made from beans, peas, etc.;
sometimes, any flour, esp. if coarse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any substance that is coarsely pulverized like meal,
but not granulated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Meal beetle</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the adult
of the meal worm. See <cref>Meal worm</cref>, below.</cd> --
<col><b>Meal moth</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a lepidopterous
insect (<spn>Asopia farinalis</spn>), the larvae of which feed upon
meal, flour, etc.</cd> -- <col><b>Meal worm</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the larva of a beetle (<spn>Tenebrio
molitor</spn>) which infests granaries, bakehouses, etc., and is very
injurious to flour and meal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Meal
<hw>Meal</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To sprinkle with, or as
with, meal.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pulverize; <as>as, <ex>mealed</ex>
powder</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mealies</ent>⟦br⟧
